Vellore Institute of Technology (VIT) has been conferred award for the best university in India for Internationalisation of Higher Education by UNICA, a network of Universities from the Capitals of Europe, with its headquarters at Brussels, Belgium. In a felicitation session of the Annual Summit meeting (UAS 2019) held recently at New Delhi, VIT vice-president, Sankar Viswanathan received the award from Vice-Consul, Embassy of the Czech Republic in New Delhi, Eva Chmelíková. Director, International Relations C. Vijayakumar and assistant director, VIT, Muhammad Rukunuddin Ghalib were also present. UNICA is an institutional network of 51 universities from 37 capital cities of Europe, which facilitates collaborations and promote academic leadership through understanding and sharing between its members throughout the European higher education area.